Message: Congrats to the village!
[[ THE SETUP ]]
finally
https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/550260631534698527/1003663297826013194/Screenshot_20220801-145914.png
let's look at this thing
[[ THE WOLF ]]

So the Wolf is blocked N1 with the orb, which they can pass. Once the wolf starts killing there are two people who won't die to their attack - their Elder friend or the protectors target. This gives some indication of who is their Elder, but not complete information (they dont even know there is a protector). Using this information plus deduction from daytime behaviour, they can use their Avsloja (confession) Rune to confess to the Elder their role, so the Elder knows their teammate. Additionally they can decide whether to get the Elder lynched to remove all village power roles or keep them around for voting parity. They have Enduring so they "might" have the opportunity to shift if lynched randomly early on.
[[ THE ELDER ]]

The Elder has a Ring of Tenacity that they can give to the wolf, when they feel sure that they know who the wolf is. This is because there are 2 disruption orbs and the village can use these to block the wolf. If the Elder and wolf have sucessfully managed to find each other, they're rewarded by making the wolf immune to block. Obviously the Elder is trying to get lynched to some extent but mustn't be too obvious about wanting to get lynched, or else people might guess that's what they're doing. I like a damned Elder as it serves a similar purpose as a Tanner, but without the game ending if the village lynch them (but there still being a pentalty for doign so). It gives the wolf a bit of cover.
[[ THE VILLAGE ]]

The village have protection, intel and an offensive role (Which can also be used to gain intel). The seer is drunk and blocked n1- I think I might have made this a non-drunk seer if I was to run this again, just because of the possibility of being blocked increased. The militia can be used as intel as if they shoot and someone doesnt die, they are either the wolf or the elder (but dont know which). They can also shoot the SS if they have managed to lose enduring on them.
[[ ITEMS ]]

If the Elder is lynched and the village lose power roles, the village still have sources of intel - the disruption orbs which can provide some information depending on where they are and if there is a kill or not. The village also start with the Tofrar (Witchcraft) Rune which at the start of the game sees 5 people as WC - The wolf, The Elder, the Protector, The seer and a villager who is Spellbound. This item is included to promote conflict in the early game but once the Elder is lynched, it becomes more powerful as the wolf will still appear as WC due to their rune (or unshifted SS). Finally there are two potions of tenacity around which can be beneficial to both the wolf and the village. They exist to help the wolf in the late game if they never got passed the Ring of Tenacity (as it might be a final 4 with 2 orbs still up), so if they manage to obtain one or both of these this is good - but they can also be used on claimed (or suspected) seers, protectors etc to prevent blocks.
[[ SO WHAT THE FUCK HAPPENED? ]]
N1: No kill, as expected, as the wolf is intentionally blocked. The Wolf chose (or forgot?) to pass the orb away so..

N2: No kill again - which had the VERY unfortunate side effect (for the village) that the Elder had been passed the orb and so looked like the wolf. Very lucky for the evil team as it meant the Elder was lynched early - though it does of course come with the downside of it now being 1 v 7 for the wolf.
N3: First night kill woo! The wolf is passed a potion of tenacity AND gets the other potion from the kill.

N4: Here's where it gets funky - the wolf has two potions of tenacity and uses one, but is still blocked by the orb. We have been blessed with a LIMITED EDITION artisan interaction, also known as a bug. This obviously is not ideal for anyone - the wolf is one kill down, the village are executing based on faulty information.
N5: The "fix for the bug" and the wolf passes their confession rune to T-rex
N6: The wolf doesn't shift T-rex so they have confessed to another villager and thus the game ends with their lynch
[[ HOW DO WE FIX THE BUG? ]]

So I talked with Modin about this throughout the day and settled on the best solution being to give the wolf a choice - they can either reclaim their missing kill with a crossbow but if they do this then we remove their enduring status (reasoning being the village would have been more likely to execute them up to that point AND it would then go to a final 3, which if they have enduring they have already won). IF they use the crossbow then the village are alerted to this fact and that they have lost enduring (so that people dont just assume the game is lost). The alternative for the wolf was do nothing and carry on from that point, in which case no message is given. The wolf chose option 2 and opted not to use the crossbow to reclaim their missing kill, which SHOULD have meant no message was given. However, Modin is a powerful God but only when he has coffee. He had not had his coffee yet and so he mistakenly sent the message even though the wolf had chosen option 2, still has enduring and didn't use the crossbow. In addition to all of this they were given a ring of tenacity since potions weren't working and they were owed two block-free nights.
This felt like the fairest solution as both sides were disadvantaged by it but it can't easily be fixed.
[[ THE OUTCOME ]]

In the end I think WHAT_so_EVER played very well - they got quite lucky in the start of the game, and the bug did bring benefits to them as well as drawbacks - but to get to the end like they did also required a lot of skill. Village also played very well, using the information they had to make the best decisions - overall I think it was a pretty balanced and interesting setup, with difficult choices and interesting dilemmas throughout, but do let me know what you thought of it.  The reason this was "more like an ext" is because in wlf games you get full information about the setup, in ext you generally do not. I couldn't put any of the other factions into a 9 player game without it being a bit "clowny" so I thought this was the best way to do it.
Hope you enjoyed - come back and play elb-133 whenever I do it :)
